# Comparison Table â€” All Control Types

---

## Preventive

**Primary Purpose:** Prevent unwanted action

**Stops Action?** Yes

**Records Events?** No

**Instructs Users?** No

**Repairs/Restores?** No

**Lab Example:** Restrict share access (remove Users permissions)

**When to use:** When you need to block unauthorized access before it happens.

---

## Detective

**Primary Purpose:** Record/log events

**Stops Action?** No

**Records Events?** Yes

**Instructs Users?** No

**Repairs/Restores?** No

**Lab Example:** Audit folder deletion (Event ID 4660/4663)

**When to use:** When you need evidence of what happened for investigations or compliance.

---

## Directive

**Primary Purpose:** Guide toward compliant behavior

**Stops Action?** No

**Records Events?** No

**Instructs Users?** Yes

**Repairs/Restores?** No

**Lab Example:** Login legal notice banner

**When to use:** When you need users to acknowledge policies before accessing systems.

---

## Corrective

**Primary Purpose:** Detect & restore secure state

**Stops Action?** No

**Records Events?** Sometimes

**Instructs Users?** No

**Repairs/Restores?** Yes

**Lab Example:** File hash check + auto-restore + BSOD

**When to use:** When you need automatic recovery from unauthorized changes or system failures.
